title: Guerrero, Branco each place 1st
text:
Guerrero, Branco each place 1st Staff reports 11:05 p.m. PDT October 21, 2015 
The Redwood Rangers had a pair of runners post a first-place finish at the second West Yosemite League cross country cluster meet of the season Wednesday at Mooney Grove Park. 
Brianna Guerrero and Laykyn Branco each won their respective race on the 3.1-mile course. 
Guerrero, a senior, won the girls race, clocking in at 19 minutes and 35 seconds, and Branco’s 16:15 paced the field in the boys event. 
In team scoring, Mt. Whitney girls finished first with 47 points followed by Redwood at second (48) and Golden West third (53). El Diamante was fifth (129). 
The Redwood boys edged Mt. Whitney 24-49 for first place. El Diamante placed third (53), and Golden West was fourth (132). 
Girls Top 10 Individual Results (3.1 miles): 1. Brianna Guerrero, 19:35, Redwood; 2. Rebecca Harris, 20:08, Golden West; 3. Fayanne Alvarado, 20:08, Golden West; 4. Tatum Perez, 20:25, Mt. Whitney; 5. Jewel Jasso, 20:33, Redwood; 6. Isabella Haberman, 20:59, Mt. Whitney; 7. Giselle Rodriguez, 21:03, Golden West; 8. Aurora Langford, 21:22, Mt. Whitney; 9. Kate Phippen, 21:23, Redwood; 10. Calla Langford, 21:25, Mt. Whitney. Team Results: 1. Mt. Whitney 47; 2. Redwood 48; 3. Golden West 53; 4. Lemoore 126; 5. El Diamante 129; 6. Hanford West 144; 7. Hanford 181. Roundup: Rangers capture Central Area girls golf title 
Boys Water Polo 
Redwood 14, Hanford 5: The Rangers improved to 7-1 in WYL action with the win Wednesday at Redwood. 
Branson Dahlenberg and Jack Terry each netted three goals, and Blake Hobbs and Drew Parsley added two apiece. Josh Ramage made 10 saves in goal. 
Hanford’s Garth Verdeggal scored four times. 
Mt. Whitney 15, El Diamante 10: Logan Mena scored a team-high seven goals in the Pioneers’ West Yosemite League victory on Tuesday at Mt. Whitney. 
Also for the Pioneers, Jakob Rodriguez tossed in three goals, and Rob Shirk had two. Jake Ruby, Jake Applegate and Philip Dinis each had one. Goalie Carter Johnson recorded 10 saves and three steals. 
For El Diamante, Mikey Diaz led the Miners with five goals. Austin Martin and Callen Bruening each had two. 
Girls Water Polo 
Hanford 12, Redwood 6: Mckenzie Darnell and Rebecca Olsen each had two goals in the Rangers’ WYL defeat in Hanford. 
Alyssa Ibarra and Taylor Harlien each tallied a goal, and goalkeeper Serina Pina had 7 saves. Roundup: GW takes fourth at D-III tourney 
Girls Volleyball 
Laton 3, Farmersville 2: Caren Moreno fired 21 kills in the Aztecs’ 25-23, 23-25, 21-25, 25-14, 15-10 East Sierra League loss Wednesday in Farmersville. 
Nicole Navarro served four aces, and Alyssa Aguilera added 15 digs for Farmersville (4-5). 
El Diamante 3, Mt. Whitney 1: The Pioneers fell 19-25, 21-25, 25-16, 14-25 in a WYL match on Tuesday. 
Isabella Luna was a force for Mt. Whitney, tallying 12 kills and 26 digs. Hailey Fletcher registered eight kills and 10 blocks, and Jill Dudle had 17 assists. 
Exeter 3, Dinuba 0: The Monarchs rolled to a 25-12, 25-11, 25-10 Central Sequoia League win on Tuesday in Exeter. 
Olivia Harden led Exeter with nine kills, five digs and four aces. Amanda Acosta added seven kills and 15 digs, and Alixis Kirkman had six kills and three blocks. 
Dinuba’s Silvia Vendejas posted five kills and six digs, and Kelsey Lowrey had three kills and five blocks. 
Walton prepared to coach 
Warriors interim head coach Luke Walton said Wednesday he was “absolutely” preparing as if he will be the head coach Tuesday for the Warriors’ regular-season opener against the New Orleans Pelicans at Oracle Arena. 
Steve Kerr did not attend the Warriors’ practice at UCLA in preparation for their preseason finale against the Los Angeles Lakers in Anaheim on Thursday, a game Kobe Bryant is doubtful to play in because of a bruised lower left leg. Read or Share this story: http://vtd-tar.co/1RXI6rx TOP VIDEOS
